PKGMAN-SEARCH(1)

# NAME

pkgman-search - search package source directories for package names

# SYNOPSIS

*pkgman search* [*-v* | *-vv*] [*--path*] [*--regex*] _expr_

# DESCRIPTION

The *pkgman search* command searches the package source directories
listed by the *pkgsrcdir* directive in *pkgman.conf*(5) for _expr_ in
package names.

The _expr_ argument may be a plain string or a regular expression in
*regex*(3) format.

The options are as follows:

*-v*
	Include the package version in the listing.

*-vv*
	Include the package version and description in the listing.

*--path*
	Include the package source path in the listing.

*--regex*
	Interpret _expr_ as a regular expression.

# EXIT STATUS

*0*
	Matches found.
*>0*
	No matches found, or an error occurred.

# SEE ALSO

*pkgman-dsearch*(1),
